text: People, QUIT BITCHING about the trailer. Trailers are SUPPOSE TO give you a series of excerpts in order to advertise a movie: https://www.google.com/#q=trailer+definition . This movie is so fucking great you do NOT need to watch the trailer. So please, skip this trailer and go watch the movie first like I did. This was seriously one of the best movies I've ever seen in my life. It's so darkly comedic in such a strong way, that after the end scene I could NOT stop laughing for at least 20 minutes straight. The ONLY time I watch trailers are when movies receive mixed reviews. This movie did not. And there are multiple elements you can't see in this trailer. I'm not going to spoil it but lets just say... something slowly progresses in the background and you don't fully realize it till the end of the movie. You don't really realize what the movie is actually saying till the end scene. And what this movie has to say is something that everyone needs to hear.
